body:
{{champion:201}} 
&quot;Mother always said - don&#039;t lose!&quot;
&quot;Mother always said - float like iceberg, sting like thrown iceberg.&quot;

I know that last line is a reference to Muhammad Ali, but assuming Braum is honest, and he really has no reason to be, he&#039;s **BRAUM**, then his mother sounds like a very confrontational woman, the kind that would suplex you into the ice if you crossed the line. Let&#039;s face it, this is the woman that gave birth to the _Heart of Freljord_, a man that wrestles dragons and punches through mountains. That Braum&#039;s mother would offer such words of encouragement like &quot;don&#039;t lose,&quot; speaks volumes about her personality. She did not tell her son, &quot;try your best&quot; or &quot;fight for what&#039;s right&quot; or even &quot;never give up,&quot; her command was a very simple &quot;don&#039;t lose.&quot; A fight breaks out? She would expect someone to hit hard like a thrown iceberg; literal of figurative, that is a monumental task, and since Braum did beat through a mountain with his bare hands, I think she was being literal. Braum&#039;s jovial disposition only makes it more amusing, considering how deadpan she sounds.

I think it is safe to say Braum&#039;s mother was a badass.

